Khartoum â€” The Council of Ministers approved, in its regular meeting Thursday headed by First Vice Presidfent of the Republic and National Prime Minister Lt. Gen. Bakri Hassan Salih, the bill of the National Council for Medical and Health professions for the year 2018, presented by the Minister of the Council of Ministers Ahmed Saad Omar. The amendment included the addition of specializations to the Council, including the establishment of standards, rules and controls for the safe practice of medical and health professions and that the violation of the Code of Professional Conduct necessitates the imposition of sanctions. The Council of Ministers also approved the bill of the Engineering Council for the year 2018, which was also submitted by the Minister of the the Council of Ministers, whereby the Engineering Council was empowered to investigate all irregularities received by the Council.